          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Data Extraction Prompt Templates"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Template 1: Entity Extraction"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " \u2b50"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "yaml"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "You are a data extraction specialist.\n\nTask: Extract all company names, dates, and monetary amounts from the following text.\n\nText:\n\"In their Q3 2024 report, TechCorp announced $2.5M revenue growth. The company, founded in 2015, reported strong performance from Microsoft and Google partnerships. Total contracts signed between July 15 and September 30, 2024, reached $1.8M.\"\n\nRequirements:\n1. Output format: JSON array\n2. Extract entities with types:\n   - company_name: Any organization mentioned\n   - date: Any date or date range\n   - monetary_amount: Any dollar amount\n3. Include source text snippet for each entity\n4. Normalize currency (remove $, M, commas)\n\nOutput:\n{\n  \"entities\": [\n    {\n      \"type\": \"company_name\",\n      \"value\": \"TechCorp\",\n      \"snippet\": \"TechCorp announced $2.5M revenue\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"type\": \"monetary_amount\",\n      \"value\": \"$2.5M\",\n      \"normalized\": 2500000,\n      \"snippet\": \"announced $2.5M revenue growth\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Template 2: Table Extraction"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " \u2b50"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "yaml"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "You are a data extraction specialist.\n\nTask: Extract the table from the following text and convert to structured data.\n\nText:\n\"Q3 Performance Metrics:\nRevenue: $5.2M (\u219115%)\nCustomers: 1,200 (\u21918%)\nRetention: 94% (\u21912%)\nChurn: 6% (\u21931%)\"\n\nRequirements:\n1. Output format: JSON array\n2. Extract metrics with:\n   - metric_name: Name of the metric\n   - value: Current value\n   - previous_value: Previous value (if available)\n   - change: Percentage change\n3. Normalize numeric values\n4. Include units where applicable\n\nOutput:\n{\n  \"metrics\": [\n    {\n      \"metric_name\": \"Revenue\",\n      \"value\": 5200000,\n      \"unit\": \"USD\",\n      \"previous_value\": 4521739,\n      \"change_percent\": 15,\n      \"change_direction\": \"\u2191\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Template 3: Invoice Extraction"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " \u2b50"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "yaml"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "You are an invoice processing specialist.\n\nDataset:\n- Source: Invoice PDFs from Q3 2024\n- Fields: invoice_id, vendor, amount, date, due_date, status\n- Records: 5,000 invoices\n\nTask: Extract invoice details from the following text.\n\nText:\n\"Invoice #INV-2024-0891\nVendor: Global Supplies Inc.\nAmount: $3,450.00\nDate: August 15, 2024\nDue Date: September 15, 2024\nStatus: Paid via credit card\"\n\nRequirements:\n1. Output format: JSON object\n2. Extract fields:\n   - invoice_id: String, format \"INV-YYYY-XXXX\"\n   - vendor: String, company name\n   - amount: Number, USD\n   - date: ISO 8601 format\n   - due_date: ISO 8601 format\n   - status: One of ['Paid', 'Pending', 'Overdue']\n3. Normalize currency (remove $, commas)\n4. Convert dates to YYYY-MM-DD\n5. Handle missing fields (set to null)\n\nConstraints:\n- Only extract valid invoice records\n- Reject if invoice_id format is invalid\n- Flag amounts > $10,000 for review\n\nValidation:\n- Verify amount is positive\n- Check date is before due_date\n- Ensure status matches payment method"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Template 4: Resume Extraction"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " \u2b50"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "yaml"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "You are a recruitment data extraction specialist.\n\nTask: Extract structured information from the following resume.\n\nResume:\n\"John Smith\nPhone: 555-123-4567\nEmail: john.smith@email.com\n\nExperience:\n- Software Engineer at TechCorp (2020-2024)\n  Built cloud applications using Python, AWS\n- Junior Developer at StartupXYZ (2018-2020)\n  Developed web applications with JavaScript\n\nEducation:\n- Bachelor of Science in Computer Science\n  University of California, 2018\n\nSkills:\nPython, JavaScript, AWS, SQL, React\"\n\nRequirements:\n1. Output format: JSON object\n2. Extract fields:\n   - name: Full name\n   - contact: phone, email\n   - experience: Array of positions\n   - education: Array of degrees\n   - skills: Array of technical skills\n3. Normalize date formats (YYYY)\n4. Extract job titles, companies, durations\n5. Categorize skills by type"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Template 5: Product Review Extraction"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " \u2b50"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "yaml"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "You are a customer analytics specialist.\n\nTask: Extract product reviews and sentiment from the following text.\n\nText:\n\"Product: Wireless Headphones Pro\nRating: 4/5 stars\nReview: 'These headphones are amazing! The sound quality is crisp and clear. Battery lasts 20 hours. Only downside is they're a bit heavy.'\nDate: 2024-09-10\nReviewer: Sarah M.\"\n\nRequirements:\n1. Output format: JSON object\n2. Extract:\n   - product_name: Product being reviewed\n   - rating: Numeric score (1-5)\n   - sentiment: Positive, Neutral, Negative\n   - review_text: Full review\n   - pros: List of positive aspects\n   - cons: List of negative aspects\n   - key_features: Mentioned features\n   - date: Review date\n   - reviewer: Reviewer name\n3. Normalize rating to decimal\n4. Extract sentiment from review text\n5. Identify pros/cons from review"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Advanced Techniques"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Technique 1: Show, Don't Just Tell (Examples)"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " \u2b50"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "\"Providing examples of desired outputs can significantly improve the quality of LLM responses.\""
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Template:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "yaml"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Extract customer names and email addresses from the following text.\n\nExample:\nText: \"Contact John Doe at john@example.com for support.\"\nOutput:\n{\n  \"name\": \"John Doe\",\n  \"email\": \"john@example.com\"\n}\n\nNow extract from:\nText: \"Reach out to Sarah Smith (sarah.smith@company.com) or Mike Johnson at mike.j@test.org.\""
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Benefits:"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "\n- "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Pattern learning"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " \u2014 Model internalizes format\n- "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Accuracy"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " \u2014 Better extraction\n- "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Consistency"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " \u2014 Same structure"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Technique 2: Domain-Specific Vocabulary"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " \u2b50"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "\"Integrate industry jargon and terminology into your prompts to guide the LLM towards domain-relevant knowledge.\""
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Template (Medical):"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "yaml"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "You are a medical data extraction specialist.\n\nTask: Extract patient diagnoses, medications, and lab results.\n\nInclude medical terminology:\n- Diagnosis codes (ICD-10)\n- Medication names (generic, brand)\n- Lab values with units (mg/dL, mmol/L)\n- Dates in ISO 8601\n\nText: \"Patient diagnosed with Type 2 Diabetes (E11.9). Prescribed Metformin 500mg BID. Glucose: 145 mg/dL (elevated).\""
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Benefits:"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "\n- "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Domain accuracy"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " \u2014 Industry-specific terms\n- "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Relevance"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " \u2014 Context-appropriate\n- "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Precision"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " \u2014 Correct terminology"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Technique 3: Prompt Chaining"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " \u2b50"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "\"Break down complex tasks into smaller steps and chain prompts together.\""
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Example flow:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "text"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Step 1: Identify entities\n\u2192 Output: List of all entities found\n\nStep 2: Classify entities\n\u2192 Input: Entities from Step 1\n\u2192 Output: Entity types (person, company, date)\n\nStep 3: Extract relationships\n\u2192 Input: Classified entities from Step 2\n\u2192 Output: Entity relationships\n\nStep 4: Build final output\n\u2192 Input: Entities and relationships from Steps 1-3\n\u2192 Output: Structured JSON"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Best Practices"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "1. Be Explicit and Specific"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " \u2b50"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "\"Be explicit: The more you define role, format, and constraints, the less 'hallucination.'\""
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Define role"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " \u2014 Data specialist, extraction expert"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Specify format"
                  },
